               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120513-67-person715">
                  ROBERT 
                  LUNN
               <interp inst="t18120513-67-person715" type="surname" value="LUNN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person715" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person715" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I was calling the hour of three in the morning, on the 8th of this month, and coming up to 
               <persName id="t18120513-67-person716">
                  Charles 
                  Cleaver
               <interp inst="t18120513-67-person716" type="surname" value="Cleaver"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person716" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person716" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            's stables I heard a noise. I thought there was somebody in the stable. I stopped and listened about five minutes. The prisoner came down and unbolted the door next to the street. He pushed it open a little way, but not quite open. I staid there about a quarter of an hour. I concluded he had seen me, and he had made his escape. I got over the wall, into the premises. I saw two bridles that had been throwed out of the window. I got out of the stables, and remained there till five o'clock. I then saw the prisoner open the loft door. I went to go in at the door I came out at. He had bolted me out. I then called 
               <persName id="t18120513-67-person717">
                  James 
                  Mann
               <interp inst="t18120513-67-person717" type="surname" value="Mann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person717" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120513-67-person717" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             to come and help me to take him. We ascended on the top of the chaise-house, and got in at the loft window, and we took the prisoner to the watchhouse, and went back again.</p>
               <p>Q. What was taken out - A. I found the bridles down in the fore court.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120513-67-person718">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WRIGHT
               <interp inst="t18120513-67-person718" type="surname" value="WRIGHT"></interp>
